-- Brazil Airline Tam Plans to Buy Brand Company Tam Milor for $96.7 Million
-- Laura Price
-- 2010-07-14T06:49:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/brazil-airline-tam-plans-to-buy-brand-company-tam-milor-for-96-7-million.html

          
          
                  July 14 (Bloomberg) --  Tam SA , the owner of Brazilâ€™s
biggest airline by market share, said its board approved a plan
to buy Tam Milor Taxi Aereo, Representacoes, Marcas e Patentes
SA for 169.9 million reais.  
 The acquisition will give it control of the Tam brands, Tam
said in a regulatory filing late yesterday. The company will buy
257,000 shares for 661 reais each. Tam said it will pay 15
percent in cash on the date the contract is signed and will pay
the remaining 85 percent in promissory notes.  
